VOICING PLAN:
- Phrase 1 (mm. 1-4): I open 5th/3rd pairs — reflecting the hushed, tender opening.
  vii° (E-Bb-E) with Bb accent adds the dark chromatic color of G#° without leaving diatonic.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 5-8): D major melody note (bar 5) treated as vi (Dm) root. C+ → V(C) substitution.
  Am (iii) carries the A-chord passages; C7=V7 diatonic.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 10-13): Dark middle section. vi(Dm)→vii°→iii(Am) path preserves the
  tonal ambiguity of the original's borrowed chords. LH has 3-note open-position voicings
  emphasizing P5 intervals in bass.
- Phrase 4 (mm. 14-17): Full recapitulation. IV(Bb) passage broadens before final V7→I.
  Final measure has 4-note LH (F2-C3-F3-A3) for full resolution.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Inner voice (RH top): C5-Bb4-A4 stepwise descent in m. 3, matching the sighing quality.
- LH bass: F→G→F (neighbor motion) in mm. 2-3 keeps bass anchored to tonic.
- Measure 16: C7 suspension with Bb in RH before final F resolution — classic harp pre-resolution.
- All Bb notes carry accid.ges="f" throughout.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-4: 2-note hands, hushed and gentle — "still, still, still" quality
- mm. 5-9: Sustained whole notes — contemplative plateau
- mm. 10-13: Moving 3-note chromatic-substitute section — inner drama, F minor coloring
- mm. 14-17: Full 4-note LH at finale, broad IV→V7→I — triumphant but gentle resolution
